What this command does

Let’s break it down carefully.

kubectl config view

This means:

“Show me my current Kubernetes configuration.”

--flatten

This is the important part.

It tells kubectl:

“Take all external file references and embed their actual contents into the output.”

So instead of:

certificate-authority: /home/kali/.minikube/ca.crt

it becomes something like:

certificate-authority-data: LS0tLS1CRUdJTi...

That long base64 text is the actual certificate content.

So the new file becomes portable.

> ~/minikube-kubeconfig-flat

This saves the output into a new file in your home directory.

So you are creating a new kubeconfig file specifically for Jenkins.


